# .cleo/.gitignore — Deny-by-default for CLEO project data
# Ignore everything, then explicitly allow only tracked files.
#
# ADR-013 §9 (2026-04-07, T5158):
#   - tasks.db / brain.db / config.json / project-info.json are NOT tracked
#     in EITHER the project git repo OR the isolated .cleo/.git checkpoint
#     repo. They are regenerated deterministically by `cleo init` and are
#     backed up via VACUUM INTO snapshots (SQLite) + atomic copies (JSON)
#     stored under .cleo/backups/. See the ADR for the full recovery story.
#   - Because git treats nested .gitignore allow rules (`!foo`) as
#     overriding parent-repo ignore rules, this file must NOT re-include
#     those four files — doing so would unignore them at the project
#     repository level and re-open the T5158 data-loss vector.

# Step 1: Ignore everything
*

# Allow list
!.gitignore
!project-context.json
!setup-otel.sh
!DATA-SAFETY-IMPLEMENTATION-SUMMARY.md
!adrs/
!adrs/**
!rcasd/
!rcasd/**
!agent-outputs/
!agent-outputs/**
!research/
!research/**
!consensus/
!consensus/**
!specs/
!specs/**

# Explicit deny safety net — databases, backups, and untracked runtime files
*.db
*.db-shm
*.db-wal
*.db-journal
config.json
project-info.json
log.json
bypass-log.json
qa-log.json
.deps-cache/
.context-alert-state.json
.context-state*.json
context-states/
.git-checkpoint-state
.migration-state.json
migrations.json
sync/
metrics/
.backups/
backups/
